-- Aixtron's $55 Million Second-Quarter Net Beats Analysts; Forecast Raised
-- Matthias Wabl
-- 2010-07-29T05:23:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/aixtron-s-55-million-second-quarter-net-beats-analysts-forecast-raised.html

          
          
             Aixtron AG, the maker of equipment
used to produce LED screens, said second-quarter net income rose
to 42.3 million euros as revenues gained, the company said in a
statement today.  
 Analysts had forecast a profit of 41.3 million euros,
according to the median of eight analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.
Aixtron now sees full-year sales at about 750 million euros and
an Ebit margin of about 33 percent, it said.  
          
          


  


        